    				Entrepreneurial Activities    			


Ramesh founded three companies, managed them in initial stages, and then turned them over to professional management. Here is a brief history of these companies.
PRAJA Inc.  1996 â€“ August 2002  San Diego, CA
Co-Founder 1996
President & CEO 1996 – June 2001
CTO July 2001- Present
PRAJA was conceived and cofounded based on research at UCSD. PRAJA inc. was the leading provider of infrastructure software technology for development of event-based information management. PRAJA worked with several big name companies, including Yahoo and GM, and several small and .com companies. According to multiple analystsâ€™ reports, PRAJA technology is unique and is far ahead of other people in information management area. PRAJA was acquired by Tibco in September 2002.
www.praja.com
Virage (NASDAQ:VRGE)  1994-2000 San Mateo, CA
Founder, CEO, and Chairman 1994-1996
Chairman 1996-1999
Director 1999-2000
The Virage platform enables the integration of streaming video with value-added applications such as advertising, pay-per-view, subscription and syndication. The Virage platform delivers cost saving and increased productivity by transforming video into easily distributed, on-demand content that enhances corporate communication, decision support and training.
Virage became a public company (NASDAQ: VRGE) in June 2000. Virage is currently the recognized leader in this growing market.
www.virage.com
ImageWare, Inc. 1991-1998 Ann Arbor, MI
Founder & Chairman (1991-1995)
Director (1995-1997)
This was Ramesh Jainâ€™s first company. This company was dedicated to linking virtual and physical worlds by providing solutions for surface modeling, reverse engineering, rapid prototyping and inspection. The company was the leader in its space and was a leader in automobile and aerospace industries. The company was acquired by SDRC in 1998. Now the leading surfacing products from SDRC are based on ImageWare products.

